Example project for mongo views plugin
======================================

1. download and install mongo_views_plugin

2. clone repository
	$ git clone git@github.com:TPTeam/mongo_views_plugin.git


3. configure Build.scala in order to find mongo views plugin
	
	$ nano {your_project_folder}/project/Build.scala
	
	Add the following line

 	val main = play.Project(appName, appVersion, appDependencies).settings(
 		line resolvers += "Local Play Repository" at "{your_play_home}/repository/local/"
 	)


4. compile
	{your_project_folder} $ play
	[mongo-views-example] $ clean
	[mongo-views-example] $ compile
	[mongo-views-example] $ run

5. open your browser to localhost:9000

6. enjoy!